{"title": "Unsanitized user input in raw HTML strings (XSS)", "summary": "  Applications should not include unsanitized user input in HTML. This can allow cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks. ", "description": "\n\nApplications should not include unsanitized user input in HTML. This\ncan allow cross-site scripting (XSS) attacks.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u274c Avoid including user input directly in HTML strings:\n\n```php\n$html = \"<h1>{$_GET[\"title\"]}</h1>\";\n```\n\n\u2705 Use a templating language such as Twig, and place the template in a separate file.\n\n\u2705 When HTML strings must be used, sanitize user input:\n\n```php\n$html = \"<h1>${htmlspecialchars($_GET[\"title\"])}</h1>\";\n```\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-79"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/php_lang_raw_html_using_user_input", "https://cheatsheetseries.owasp.org/cheatsheets/Cross_Site_Scripting_Prevention_Cheat_Sheet.html"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}